            <text type="letter" decls="#corresp1">
                <body>
                    

<lb/>not like the bow's classical spelling as much as
<lb/>a pr so am very careful in my selection of
<lb/>words, but how I hate the inexpressive
<lb/>Artillery activity when I know what it
<lb/>really means from actual experience. </p>
<p>My typing clerk has been rather lazy
<lb/>&amp; I am being held up in consequence, very
<lb/>annoying as I feel the days gaining on me
<lb/>but I mean to have a real set to again
<lb/>this afternoon so as to finish July by the
<lb/>end of this! week. It would make it so 
<lb/>much easier to have a certain lady typist!</p>
<p>I am amused at Greatmen's little foibles: &#x2014;
        
    

    
         
        <pb n="6500" facs="#L1916_2346_img_6500"/>
        
        
           
            <lb/>Butler's I have described, Sir DH's is his golf
<lb/>the one <del>game</del> <add>thing</add> at which he is perhaps rather behind
<lb/>his contemporaries tho my no means a bad
<lb/>player. They say that he would rather get
<lb/>a reduction of 4 in his handicap than an
<lb/>O M Garter or whatever particular decoration
<lb/>he still lacks.</p>
<p>Kiggell's simplicity is very striking he will
<lb/>continually hold a young officer's horse whilst he
<lb/>speaks to the Chief without thinking it in the
<lb/>least <foreign>infra dig</foreign></p>. 
<p>I hear from Douglas that
<lb/>security in Belfast is improving but that outside
<lb/>the Sinn Feiners <unclear>discountenance</unclear> any security
<lb/>meetings!</p>
